1
00:00:05,638 --> 00:00:07,368
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,438 --> 00:00:08,938
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,008 --> 00:00:11,678
(Episode 33)

4
00:00:12,378 --> 00:00:15,278
Gosh, I hope
she'll at least eat some of these.

5
00:00:17,218 --> 00:00:18,318
This is so good.

6
00:00:18,318 --> 00:00:20,688
- Isn't it so tasty?
- What? What the...

7
00:00:20,688 --> 00:00:21,918
Try the tteokbokki, too. Here.

8
00:00:22,218 --> 00:00:25,488
Is that punk really on a date?
Who is that?

9
00:00:25,758 --> 00:00:28,258
- Okay, let me see her face.
- Like this.

10
00:00:30,358 --> 00:00:31,358
So pretty.

11
00:00:34,068 --> 00:00:36,098
- We're out of pickled radish.
- I'll get more.

12
00:00:36,098 --> 00:00:37,668
No, let me. I'll get it.
You stay here.

13
00:00:37,738 --> 00:00:39,368
- I can get it.
- No, I've got it.

14
00:00:43,878 --> 00:00:44,878
Jeong Han...

15
00:00:53,748 --> 00:00:54,818
Wait inside.

16
00:00:57,318 --> 00:00:58,318
Hey.

17
00:00:58,858 --> 00:01:00,258
Jeong Han...

18
00:01:00,658 --> 00:01:02,098
Hey, hold on. Come here.

19
00:01:02,098 --> 00:01:03,528
Hey, just for a second.

20
00:01:03,598 --> 00:01:04,698
Just a second, come over here.

21
00:01:05,098 --> 00:01:07,568
- Let go of me.
- Hold on. Hey, just hear me out.

22
00:01:07,568 --> 00:01:08,868
Seriously! I said let go of me,
you brat!

23
00:01:09,168 --> 00:01:12,808
- Hey, look, it's...
- Hey, Gong Dae Han.

24
00:01:13,868 --> 00:01:16,838
What did I just see?

25
00:01:17,308 --> 00:01:20,778
Don't tell me
your girlfriend is Dong Suk.

26
00:01:22,718 --> 00:01:23,778
Yes.

27
00:01:24,878 --> 00:01:28,248
- You little punk!
- My gosh. Hey, that hurts.

28
00:01:28,888 --> 00:01:32,288
Of all the women in the world,
it had to be Dong Suk?

29
00:01:32,558 --> 00:01:33,558
Why?

30
00:01:34,328 --> 00:01:37,758
- What's wrong with Dong Suk? Why?
- Who said something's wrong?

31
00:01:38,028 --> 00:01:41,098
Hey, you. Have you lost your mind?

32
00:01:41,098 --> 00:01:42,998
I haven't lost my mind, Jeong Han.

33
00:01:44,868 --> 00:01:46,738
I'm just following my heart.

34
00:01:46,808 --> 00:01:51,038
You're dating the ex-wife of the man
your ex-wife cheated on you with?

35
00:01:51,108 --> 00:01:53,078
We bonded over our shared pain.
That can happen, you know.

36
00:01:53,078 --> 00:01:54,548
Cut the nonsense!

37
00:01:54,908 --> 00:01:59,588
Hey, if Mom and Seong Mi find out,
everything will blow up.

38
00:01:59,818 --> 00:02:03,118
And don't you know this is
a critical time for Seong Mi?

39
00:02:03,658 --> 00:02:05,588
Gosh, I know...

40
00:02:06,028 --> 00:02:09,228
I know. That's why
I kept it a secret, Jeong Han.

41
00:02:09,228 --> 00:02:11,498
Whatever.
Just break up with her. Now.

42
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:14,598
No. Jeong Han,
I really can't break up with her.

43
00:02:14,868 --> 00:02:18,598
How can you say that to me?
I really can't break up with her.

44
00:02:18,768 --> 00:02:21,708
Is that so?
Should I tell Bucket, then?

45
00:02:21,768 --> 00:02:23,978
Do you want to get beaten to a pulp?

46
00:02:24,038 --> 00:02:26,678
He likes me. You have no idea
how good I've been to him.

47
00:02:27,108 --> 00:02:30,718
So you... Is that why
you've been acting as his spy?

48
00:02:31,048 --> 00:02:33,988
To get on his good side
so you could date Dong Suk?

49
00:02:35,588 --> 00:02:38,758
What were you thinking,
pulling a crazy stunt like that?

50
00:02:39,058 --> 00:02:42,328
You cut it out right now.
Understand?

51
00:02:53,168 --> 00:02:55,138
Wait, my dad found out?

52
00:02:55,608 --> 00:02:58,008
And after I promised
I'd be careful...

53
00:02:58,848 --> 00:02:59,848
Sorry.

54
00:03:02,178 --> 00:03:03,778
My dad must be furious.

55
00:03:05,078 --> 00:03:08,048
He's been a bit on edge lately
because of Mom.

56
00:03:21,128 --> 00:03:23,398
(My Endorphin)

57
00:03:36,178 --> 00:03:37,178
What's wrong?

58
00:03:38,678 --> 00:03:39,918
Is it not sitting well?

59
00:03:40,788 --> 00:03:44,388
It's not sitting well with me.
But the first bite was delicious.

60
00:03:44,888 --> 00:03:47,528
Should I get you
something else then?

61
00:03:47,858 --> 00:03:51,458
No, it's fine. You have patients.
You should get going.

62
00:03:51,698 --> 00:03:52,868
You too, Mother.

63
00:03:53,498 --> 00:03:57,338
It's harder on me if everyone's life
gets disrupted because of me.

64
00:03:57,638 --> 00:04:01,068
Fine. I'll be back as soon as I can,
all right?

65
00:04:01,068 --> 00:04:03,178
Okay. Honey.

66
00:04:03,338 --> 00:04:06,548
Here, take these dumplings
for Dae Han, okay?

67
00:04:06,908 --> 00:04:09,778
Oh, Dae Han is...

68
00:04:10,418 --> 00:04:12,148
He already had dumplings.

69
00:04:12,988 --> 00:04:14,548
With his girlfriend.

70
00:04:14,888 --> 00:04:17,318
Really? Did you see who she is?

71
00:04:18,458 --> 00:04:21,058
- I did.
- Who? Who is she?

72
00:04:21,758 --> 00:04:24,858
Come on, tell me already.
I'm dying to know.

73
00:04:25,458 --> 00:04:26,468
It's...

74
00:04:27,198 --> 00:04:28,998
Dong Suk.

75
00:04:29,498 --> 00:04:30,838
Yang Dong Suk.

76
00:04:31,598 --> 00:04:33,708
- What?
- Who?

77
00:04:34,138 --> 00:04:36,978
Bucket's sister, Yang Dong Suk.

78
00:04:37,838 --> 00:04:39,008
Are you serious?

79
00:04:39,748 --> 00:04:42,048
You're joking, right?
You have to be.

80
00:04:43,048 --> 00:04:45,648
Yes, I... I was just trying
to make you laugh.

81
00:04:45,718 --> 00:04:47,518
I was just pulling your leg.
Oh, man.

82
00:04:47,588 --> 00:04:49,588
- Come on. What was that for?
- Ouch, sorry.

83
00:04:49,658 --> 00:04:52,758
Why would you joke like that?
You're just stressing out Seong Mi.

84
00:04:52,858 --> 00:04:56,698
I know, right? I feel nauseous now.

85
00:04:57,028 --> 00:04:59,628
So, did you even see
your brother's girlfriend?

86
00:04:59,898 --> 00:05:03,798
No, you know what?
Pickled radish is great for nausea.

87
00:05:03,938 --> 00:05:05,868
- Have some pickled radish. Eat up.
- Honestly.

88
00:05:05,868 --> 00:05:07,368
- Gosh, unbelievable.
- Here.

89
00:05:08,608 --> 00:05:10,838
- Right...
- You really gave me a scare.

90
00:05:10,908 --> 00:05:12,978
Of all the things to joke about.
Seriously.

91
00:06:00,728 --> 00:06:02,128
Mom.

92
00:06:08,028 --> 00:06:09,038
My girl...

93
00:06:09,498 --> 00:06:10,898
Mom...

94
00:06:13,308 --> 00:06:14,408
My daughter...

95
00:06:47,168 --> 00:06:48,838
Don't cry, Mom.

96
00:06:49,808 --> 00:06:51,308
This is a happy day.

97
00:06:59,288 --> 00:07:00,418
Sweetheart,

98
00:07:01,788 --> 00:07:03,158
you weren't mad at me?

99
00:07:04,488 --> 00:07:05,488
No.

100
00:07:06,588 --> 00:07:07,828
I was never mad at you.

101
00:07:11,058 --> 00:07:12,328
That time...

102
00:07:15,738 --> 00:07:18,098
when the Sister called,

103
00:07:19,568 --> 00:07:21,538
the reason I said what I did...

104
00:07:22,678 --> 00:07:23,938
was because if we stayed in touch,

105
00:07:24,838 --> 00:07:26,908
I was afraid I'd want to see you.

106
00:07:28,008 --> 00:07:29,818
I made a point not to ask
where you lived,

107
00:07:30,978 --> 00:07:32,818
or which country you moved to.

108
00:07:34,718 --> 00:07:36,088
I never asked.

109
00:07:37,258 --> 00:07:38,558
Because if I knew,

110
00:07:39,958 --> 00:07:41,658
I was afraid
I'd miss you too much...

111
00:07:42,998 --> 00:07:44,228
and come looking for you.

112
00:07:46,568 --> 00:07:47,598
All I did...

113
00:07:48,498 --> 00:07:49,968
was ask them to let me know...

114
00:07:50,538 --> 00:07:52,568
if you were doing okay.

115
00:07:54,738 --> 00:07:57,408
But you never forgot about me
for a second, did you?

116
00:07:59,108 --> 00:08:00,478
Not for one single moment.

117
00:08:02,048 --> 00:08:03,878
You never forgot about me.

118
00:08:04,978 --> 00:08:07,388
You still celebrate my birthday,

119
00:08:08,388 --> 00:08:10,258
and you still have my picture.

120
00:08:12,528 --> 00:08:13,628
I...

121
00:08:16,698 --> 00:08:17,998
tried everything I could...

122
00:08:20,698 --> 00:08:22,498
to raise you myself.

123
00:08:24,268 --> 00:08:27,268
But I had no education,

124
00:08:27,808 --> 00:08:29,338
and I had nothing.

125
00:08:31,808 --> 00:08:33,478
I was too young back then,

126
00:08:36,048 --> 00:08:37,448
and so incredibly immature.

127
00:08:40,118 --> 00:08:41,788
Even if I could go back in time,

128
00:08:44,358 --> 00:08:45,888
I'd still have to let you go.

129
00:08:49,698 --> 00:08:51,098
Thanks to you, Mom,

130
00:08:52,398 --> 00:08:54,768
I met wonderful adoptive parents.

131
00:08:55,768 --> 00:08:58,268
I always had food to eat
and clothes to wear.

132
00:08:58,798 --> 00:09:01,138
I never once wanted for anything.

133
00:09:01,908 --> 00:09:03,978
I got to study and travel,

134
00:09:05,008 --> 00:09:06,778
and do everything I wanted.

135
00:09:07,778 --> 00:09:08,978
Thank you.

136
00:09:09,948 --> 00:09:11,248
For growing up to be so beautiful,

137
00:09:11,978 --> 00:09:13,618
so lovely,

138
00:09:14,988 --> 00:09:17,058
and so smart.

139
00:09:20,788 --> 00:09:23,328
To think that I'm the daughter...

140
00:09:23,858 --> 00:09:26,068
of someone so beautiful and lovely,

141
00:09:27,298 --> 00:09:28,498
it makes me so incredibly happy.

142
00:09:30,238 --> 00:09:31,368
And...

143
00:09:32,838 --> 00:09:35,268
seeing how happy you are now...

144
00:09:36,308 --> 00:09:37,838
I'm so glad I got to see it.

145
00:09:40,808 --> 00:09:42,408
Thank you so much for that.

146
00:09:44,178 --> 00:09:45,248
Thank you.

147
00:09:46,788 --> 00:09:48,418
For you to say that...

148
00:09:49,858 --> 00:09:52,258
I'm so grateful, Veronica.

149
00:10:08,768 --> 00:10:11,838
(Korean Medicine Doctor
Yang Dong Ik)

150
00:10:12,408 --> 00:10:16,778
She saved every penny she could
for that kid.

151
00:10:17,178 --> 00:10:19,318
She wanted to save up a large sum
so she could someday...

152
00:10:19,318 --> 00:10:21,488
be a real mother to her daughter.

153
00:10:21,918 --> 00:10:25,318
She's still saving for that dream,
isn't she?

154
00:10:26,058 --> 00:10:28,558
The child must have grown up by now.

155
00:10:32,698 --> 00:10:34,568
Did you handle
Se Ri's building purchase contract?

156
00:10:35,328 --> 00:10:36,338
Not yet.

157
00:10:36,938 --> 00:10:39,968
Apparently, Se Ri forgot to bring
her ID and personal seal.

158
00:10:40,808 --> 00:10:43,608
I'll call the real estate office
and reschedule.

159
00:10:45,178 --> 00:10:46,308
All right, then.

160
00:10:54,148 --> 00:10:58,158
(Korean Medicine Doctor
Yang Dong Ik)

161
00:11:02,488 --> 00:11:03,498
Hey, Hyun Bin.

162
00:11:04,428 --> 00:11:07,368
Could you come down to Onjeong
after work today?

163
00:11:08,828 --> 00:11:09,968
Yes.

164
00:11:10,598 --> 00:11:12,198
There's something I need
to talk to you about.

165
00:11:15,438 --> 00:11:18,078
Okay. Sure, Dad. All right.

166
00:11:25,078 --> 00:11:26,088
Director.

167
00:11:28,988 --> 00:11:30,658
Has Dr. Han been discharged?

168
00:11:31,018 --> 00:11:33,228
Yes, this morning.

169
00:11:34,488 --> 00:11:37,358
Back to being formal, I see.

170
00:11:39,028 --> 00:11:40,168
It's only right.

171
00:11:41,098 --> 00:11:42,098
I guess so.

172
00:11:42,498 --> 00:11:44,938
Then, shall we go
to the design team meeting?

173
00:11:45,438 --> 00:11:48,008
Yes, let's.

174
00:11:53,378 --> 00:11:56,078
I think I like it more because
it's not a raglan sleeve.

175
00:11:56,818 --> 00:12:00,588
Exactly. That's the whole point.
It makes the waist more accentuated.

176
00:12:04,918 --> 00:12:08,088
Gosh, seriously.
Why is the mood in here so tense?

177
00:12:08,488 --> 00:12:12,828
The fashion show went great,
and Dr. Han left the hospital.

178
00:12:13,728 --> 00:12:15,028
Oh, I wonder why.

179
00:12:15,298 --> 00:12:17,098
You two went public
with your relationship right here.

180
00:12:17,768 --> 00:12:19,608
But Director Yang's leaving,
and you broke up.

181
00:12:19,608 --> 00:12:21,408
Did you expect us to celebrate?

182
00:12:22,238 --> 00:12:24,238
I'm sorry for making things
awkward for everyone.

183
00:12:24,538 --> 00:12:26,348
I'll make sure
it doesn't affect our work.

184
00:12:27,878 --> 00:12:29,678
My goodness.

185
00:12:30,618 --> 00:12:33,688
So Hye, can you think of anything
to lighten the mood?

186
00:12:33,948 --> 00:12:36,258
I'm uncomfortable
being the center of attention.

187
00:12:38,018 --> 00:12:41,158
Hey, why don't you go ahead and brag
about that job offer you got?

188
00:12:41,658 --> 00:12:42,658
A job offer?

189
00:12:43,328 --> 00:12:44,328
From where?

190
00:12:44,798 --> 00:12:49,168
I got an offer from Ceviel
to be their Creative Director.

191
00:12:49,738 --> 00:12:50,798
Ceviel?

192
00:12:51,338 --> 00:12:53,668
Wow, they're our biggest competitor.
They have some nerve.

193
00:12:54,738 --> 00:12:58,938
Don't tell me
you're leaving too, Ms. Gong.

194
00:12:59,348 --> 00:13:02,818
Of course not. After all the work
we put into building up FG.

195
00:13:03,618 --> 00:13:07,548
Besides, once we go global,
we'll be bigger than Ceviel.

196
00:13:17,158 --> 00:13:18,298
(Hwangbo Hye Su, Vice President,
Strategic Planning Division)

197
00:13:19,398 --> 00:13:21,598
You'll be transitioning your work
to Managing Director Hong Jae Pil.

198
00:13:21,998 --> 00:13:23,038
Managing Director Hong?

199
00:13:23,668 --> 00:13:25,868
He's one of Director Baek's cronies
from Strategic Management.

200
00:13:26,068 --> 00:13:27,238
It's not your problem anymore,

201
00:13:27,238 --> 00:13:29,138
so why care
if it all goes down the drain?

202
00:13:29,878 --> 00:13:32,008
Isn't this what you signed up for
when you decided to quit?

203
00:13:32,078 --> 00:13:34,378
Come on. Do you have to make things
so uncomfortable for me?

204
00:13:35,248 --> 00:13:36,248
And one more thing.

205
00:13:37,218 --> 00:13:40,818
Claramont in Paris is insisting
that Pacu Nacho stay on the project.

206
00:13:40,888 --> 00:13:42,388
They've made it a condition
of the contract.

207
00:13:43,318 --> 00:13:46,558
But of course, you'll refuse, right?
Since you're quitting.

208
00:13:52,158 --> 00:13:55,668
I guess we have no choice
but to scrap our Paris expansion.

209
00:13:56,398 --> 00:13:58,898
I already made a promise,
and I can't go back on it.

210
00:13:59,738 --> 00:14:01,168
Your threats are useless.

211
00:14:04,108 --> 00:14:05,638
Even the threats didn't work?

212
00:14:07,808 --> 00:14:08,908
No.

213
00:14:10,278 --> 00:14:14,118
But is the situation
really that dire?

214
00:14:14,318 --> 00:14:15,318
No.

215
00:14:15,788 --> 00:14:18,318
I was just playing
the sympathy card.

216
00:14:19,888 --> 00:14:23,298
Wow, you really want to hold on
to Director Yang that badly?

217
00:14:24,098 --> 00:14:26,298
It's partly for the sake
of the business.

218
00:14:26,728 --> 00:14:30,298
If Pacu Nacho and Ms. Gong team up,
even if it feels awkward at first,

219
00:14:30,368 --> 00:14:32,468
another solution
might present itself.

220
00:14:34,608 --> 00:14:39,408
I see your point, Vice President.
I'll go have a word with Ms. Gong.

221
00:14:42,818 --> 00:14:43,818
The chewy cookie.

222
00:14:44,318 --> 00:14:47,688
- What?
- Park, are you with Director Baek?

223
00:14:48,948 --> 00:14:49,958
What?

224
00:14:50,058 --> 00:14:52,788
Why did you give the Chairman
the chewy cookie? Why?

225
00:14:53,458 --> 00:14:58,258
I hope that didn't get you
in trouble. Did it?

226
00:14:58,428 --> 00:14:59,428
It's bad.

227
00:15:00,168 --> 00:15:04,238
He's drifting, and when he's lucid,
he just keeps saying "chewy cookie."

228
00:15:04,798 --> 00:15:08,668
I'm a nervous wreck,
thinking he's going to choke on it.

229
00:15:09,878 --> 00:15:10,978
I'm so sorry.

230
00:15:11,438 --> 00:15:16,218
The truth is,
it reminded me of my late mother.

231
00:15:17,318 --> 00:15:18,748
Right before she passed away,

232
00:15:18,748 --> 00:15:20,988
she had no appetite
but craved ramyeon.

233
00:15:21,548 --> 00:15:25,858
I regret saying it was unhealthy
and not letting her have any.

234
00:15:28,428 --> 00:15:30,798
Anyway, I'm truly sorry,
Vice President.

235
00:15:32,998 --> 00:15:34,568
The Chairman wants to see you.

236
00:15:36,668 --> 00:15:39,638
- Me? Why? What for?
- Why do you think?

237
00:15:40,338 --> 00:15:41,868
He wants you
to bring him something tasty.

238
00:15:42,168 --> 00:15:44,278
Another trendy snack.
Not the chewy cookie.

239
00:15:46,308 --> 00:15:47,908
Oh, my.

240
00:15:48,908 --> 00:15:49,948
This is a tough one.

241
00:15:52,888 --> 00:15:56,048
Is it true?
Is the global deal in trouble?

242
00:15:56,258 --> 00:15:57,618
Of course, it is.

243
00:15:57,618 --> 00:16:01,058
Hey, it'd be so embarrassing
if the deal falls through.

244
00:16:01,228 --> 00:16:05,698
Even if it's awkward, you need
to work with Director Yang. Got it?

245
00:16:06,268 --> 00:16:10,798
But after his difficult decision,
what am I supposed to do?

246
00:16:10,868 --> 00:16:15,168
Beg him. Say you can't break up.
That you can never, ever break up.

247
00:16:15,168 --> 00:16:16,168
Hey.

248
00:16:17,038 --> 00:16:19,178
You really can't do this one thing
for the company?

249
00:16:19,338 --> 00:16:21,648
Are you just going to sit back
and watch us all go down?

250
00:16:21,878 --> 00:16:25,818
Are we just going to reuse designs
every season like we used to?

251
00:16:26,148 --> 00:16:28,388
I don't want to go back to that.
Okay?

252
00:16:28,388 --> 00:16:29,518
Hey, Ms. Gong.

253
00:16:29,518 --> 00:16:32,088
- Is this the best you can do?
- Will you just be quiet?

254
00:16:32,788 --> 00:16:34,088
Unbelievable.

255
00:16:36,258 --> 00:16:38,458
I'll give him this.
Mr. Park is a convincing liar.

256
00:16:38,698 --> 00:16:39,928
It was a lie?

257
00:16:40,098 --> 00:16:43,538
Of course. He's just pressuring you
into keeping me around.

258
00:16:43,868 --> 00:16:48,308
Gosh, Park Jun Hyeok.
How does he lie so convincingly?

259
00:16:48,408 --> 00:16:51,308
He's picking it up from the VP
since they're friends now.

260
00:16:51,408 --> 00:16:53,308
Now, he's always like,
"The VP and I are friends."

261
00:16:53,408 --> 00:16:55,478
He's always pulling that defiant act
on me.

262
00:17:02,018 --> 00:17:06,728
You know what makes the breakup feel
more real than the formal language?

263
00:17:09,158 --> 00:17:12,598
I feel like I used to be the first
to hear your good news, but...

264
00:17:15,468 --> 00:17:18,768
Anyway,
congratulations on the offer.

265
00:17:18,768 --> 00:17:20,438
You're becoming a big shot.

266
00:17:23,138 --> 00:17:24,908
It's all thanks to you, Director.

267
00:17:25,438 --> 00:17:27,508
If I do any interviews,
I'll be sure to give you a shoutout.

268
00:17:31,918 --> 00:17:34,388
(3H Acupressure Bed)

269
00:17:39,888 --> 00:17:43,358
Wow, it's true what they say.
The apple really doesn't fall far.

270
00:17:43,558 --> 00:17:46,868
You two look so alike,
especially the way you smile.

271
00:17:49,228 --> 00:17:53,568
But you're just like Mom inside.
So honest and loving.

272
00:17:53,868 --> 00:17:55,608
- Really?
- Yes.

273
00:17:56,378 --> 00:18:00,148
I wish I had Mom's looks, though.
I could've entered a beauty pageant.

274
00:18:00,848 --> 00:18:02,148
What are you talking about?

275
00:18:02,148 --> 00:18:04,578
You're so beautiful and lovely,
sweetheart.

276
00:18:05,878 --> 00:18:08,118
Eun Bin, thank you so much.

277
00:18:08,688 --> 00:18:10,318
If it weren't for you,

278
00:18:11,218 --> 00:18:14,728
I would've left without ever really
understanding how Mom felt.

279
00:18:15,158 --> 00:18:18,398
I know, right? Gosh, if I'd known,
I would have said something sooner.

280
00:18:20,098 --> 00:18:22,998
Hey, before Min Seo leaves,
should the three of us go on a trip?

281
00:18:27,208 --> 00:18:30,578
If we could,
I would love that so much.

282
00:18:38,378 --> 00:18:41,618
Honey, I brought my seal and my ID.

283
00:18:42,648 --> 00:18:43,658
Yes, about that.

284
00:18:44,788 --> 00:18:47,258
Apparently, there's an issue
with the building.

285
00:18:47,858 --> 00:18:52,758
- We may have to postpone or cancel.
- Really?

286
00:18:54,098 --> 00:18:55,098
Why?

287
00:18:55,568 --> 00:18:56,668
Are you disappointed?

288
00:18:57,238 --> 00:18:58,368
Of course.

289
00:18:58,668 --> 00:19:00,038
You can't just give me something
and take it back.

290
00:19:01,438 --> 00:19:02,638
By the way, you...

291
00:19:04,138 --> 00:19:05,638
Didn't you say
you had something to tell me?

292
00:19:05,708 --> 00:19:07,808
Oh, I'll tell you at home later.

293
00:19:08,078 --> 00:19:09,948
But you said
you had something to tell me, too.

294
00:19:10,248 --> 00:19:12,478
I have plans today.

295
00:19:12,848 --> 00:19:14,588
You won't stay out late
drinking again, right?

296
00:19:15,248 --> 00:19:16,288
I'll be home early.

297
00:19:16,958 --> 00:19:18,888
Then I'll wait for you at home.

298
00:19:22,788 --> 00:19:25,058
(Korean Medicine Doctor
Yang Dong Ik)

299
00:19:31,538 --> 00:19:34,208
This is Yang Dong Ik.

300
00:19:35,508 --> 00:19:36,578
There are a few more things...

301
00:19:37,408 --> 00:19:38,508
I need you to look into.

302
00:19:41,778 --> 00:19:42,778
Hey.

303
00:19:43,348 --> 00:19:45,548
I drafted a manual therapy plan
for our patient, Kim Chang Seok.

304
00:19:45,618 --> 00:19:47,618
Leave it there. I'll check tomorrow.

305
00:19:47,618 --> 00:19:48,618
Wait, Jeong Han.

306
00:19:49,448 --> 00:19:50,718
Come on, just talk to me.

307
00:19:51,388 --> 00:19:54,428
What's there to talk about?
We've already been over this.

308
00:19:54,628 --> 00:19:56,628
I really can't break up
with Dong Suk.

309
00:19:57,428 --> 00:19:59,428
I can't live without her, Jeong Han.

310
00:20:00,628 --> 00:20:02,928
- Then don't.
- Hey!

311
00:20:02,998 --> 00:20:04,198
I said, it's not happening!

312
00:20:05,098 --> 00:20:07,438
Don't you dare bring this up again.
Got it?

313
00:20:15,578 --> 00:20:16,878
What did Dr. Gong say?

314
00:20:17,248 --> 00:20:18,448
Did he say
we have to break up immediately?

315
00:20:19,618 --> 00:20:20,618
No.

316
00:20:21,388 --> 00:20:22,548
I think he was just
a little shocked.

317
00:20:23,158 --> 00:20:26,018
You know how close we are.
He'll come around.

318
00:20:26,418 --> 00:20:28,828
Besides, his wife is sick,
so he's just on edge.

319
00:20:29,828 --> 00:20:33,298
You should've just denied it.

320
00:20:34,028 --> 00:20:36,298
We had to cross that bridge
eventually.

321
00:20:37,498 --> 00:20:39,808
My family would flip out
if they found out, wouldn't they?

322
00:20:45,078 --> 00:20:46,308
Dong Suk, didn't I tell you?

323
00:20:47,208 --> 00:20:50,118
No matter what thorny path
lies before us,

324
00:20:50,178 --> 00:20:51,418
I promised
never to let go of your hand...

325
00:20:51,418 --> 00:20:52,578
and that we would get through it.

326
00:20:54,118 --> 00:20:55,118
Uncle.

327
00:20:55,518 --> 00:20:56,758
Hey, Woo Jae.

328
00:21:00,588 --> 00:21:01,628
There was something on her hand.

329
00:21:02,688 --> 00:21:04,858
Let's talk inside.
Someone might see.

330
00:21:06,228 --> 00:21:07,628
Woo Jae already knows.

331
00:21:15,908 --> 00:21:16,908
Woo Jae.

332
00:21:17,938 --> 00:21:18,978
I practically raised you.

333
00:21:19,038 --> 00:21:21,108
I know. Just get inside. Come on.

334
00:21:24,978 --> 00:21:28,748
Don't worry about Mother's case.
Before I leave for Argentina,

335
00:21:28,818 --> 00:21:31,188
I'll make sure
the adoption goes through smoothly.

336
00:21:32,388 --> 00:21:34,758
It's turning out to be harder
than I expected.

337
00:21:35,058 --> 00:21:36,928
We have to contact our birth mother
and everything.

338
00:21:39,258 --> 00:21:40,528
How much do you trust Se Ri?

339
00:21:41,598 --> 00:21:46,138
Here we go again.
Dad, please stop this and get help.

340
00:21:46,438 --> 00:21:48,238
I wondered
if the problem was me, too.

341
00:21:48,638 --> 00:21:50,808
I even had your grandfather
prepare some herbal medicine for me.

342
00:21:51,308 --> 00:21:53,378
- But...
- But what?

343
00:21:54,308 --> 00:21:55,578
Before she married me,

344
00:21:57,518 --> 00:21:58,778
Se Ri had a daughter.

345
00:21:59,918 --> 00:22:02,218
- What?
- When she was pregnant,

346
00:22:02,618 --> 00:22:04,058
the baby's father died,

347
00:22:04,558 --> 00:22:05,988
and she gave the baby up
for adoption.

348
00:22:09,928 --> 00:22:10,928
I've been duped.

349
00:22:12,298 --> 00:22:13,598
I've been lied to this entire time.

350
00:22:15,368 --> 00:22:17,168
So you thought
she had never been married before,

351
00:22:17,168 --> 00:22:19,038
but it was her second marriage?

352
00:22:21,568 --> 00:22:25,878
But Dad, you had Eun Bin and me.
You remarried, too.

353
00:22:25,938 --> 00:22:27,748
It seems a little unfair
to make an issue of her past.

354
00:22:28,108 --> 00:22:29,108
Fine.

355
00:22:29,448 --> 00:22:31,818
I tried my best
to understand that part.

356
00:22:32,418 --> 00:22:34,618
You know how I feel about people
who abandon their children.

357
00:22:35,888 --> 00:22:38,588
And our whole family
is traumatized by it.

358
00:22:38,588 --> 00:22:40,858
So I tried to understand
why she had to hide it.

359
00:22:41,428 --> 00:22:42,428
But...

360
00:22:44,728 --> 00:22:46,428
That daughter of hers
is living in our house.

361
00:22:47,998 --> 00:22:52,168
- What?
- It's Min Seo, their English tutor.

362
00:22:53,868 --> 00:22:55,008
She's Cha Se Ri's daughter.

363
00:22:57,108 --> 00:22:59,208
I asked around at the salon
where Se Ri used to work.

364
00:22:59,738 --> 00:23:01,178
They said
she wanted to be a proper mother...

365
00:23:01,178 --> 00:23:02,778
by making sure
her daughter was set for life.

366
00:23:03,248 --> 00:23:06,548
But how could she be so conniving
to bring her own daughter here?

367
00:23:07,248 --> 00:23:08,318
Se Ri...

368
00:23:09,088 --> 00:23:10,288
She never loved me.

369
00:23:10,888 --> 00:23:14,628
She married me for my money
to try and turn her life around.

370
00:23:15,328 --> 00:23:16,528
And you didn't realize that?

371
00:23:17,598 --> 00:23:18,598
What?

372
00:23:18,598 --> 00:23:21,598
Why would
a young former beauty queen...

373
00:23:21,628 --> 00:23:26,098
marry a father of two
after only a month of dating?

374
00:23:26,638 --> 00:23:29,068
You were looking for a young,
pretty woman too, weren't you?

375
00:23:29,368 --> 00:23:32,238
Plus, someone who would take care
of her widowed father-in-law...

376
00:23:32,378 --> 00:23:34,508
and be a good mother to your kids,
someone who came from a poor family.

377
00:23:35,648 --> 00:23:39,148
- Still, she should have told me.
- Why? So you could react like this?

378
00:23:41,618 --> 00:23:42,618
But wait.

379
00:23:43,618 --> 00:23:45,488
How did you find
all this out anyway?

380
00:23:47,228 --> 00:23:49,758
- A private investigator.
- Dad, seriously!

381
00:23:49,998 --> 00:23:51,428
I was suspicious of her
and had to act.

382
00:23:51,498 --> 00:23:55,098
If you're so suspicious,
you should just ask her directly.

383
00:23:55,828 --> 00:23:57,068
I was going to.

384
00:23:58,138 --> 00:24:00,768
That's why I asked to see you first.

385
00:24:00,908 --> 00:24:03,038
Good thing you did.

386
00:24:03,378 --> 00:24:06,178
You'd have started a huge fight.

387
00:24:06,178 --> 00:24:09,248
Just be calm and ask her nicely.
Got it?

388
00:24:09,948 --> 00:24:10,948
Yes.

389
00:24:11,248 --> 00:24:13,888
Even if it's true,

390
00:24:13,888 --> 00:24:15,448
you're not going to get
another divorce, are you?

391
00:24:17,388 --> 00:24:20,428
She's never going to leave you.

392
00:24:20,888 --> 00:24:24,158
Because from what I can see,
she genuinely loves you.

393
00:24:25,498 --> 00:24:29,698
- You think so?
- Of course. Don't be scared.

394
00:24:29,768 --> 00:24:32,038
Just ask her what happened
and hear her out.

395
00:24:32,638 --> 00:24:35,538
And then, we can talk again. Okay?

396
00:24:41,678 --> 00:24:44,818
Min Seo, what's the one thing
you most wanted to do with your mom?

397
00:24:46,848 --> 00:24:50,388
- A trip?
- That was my idea. Tell me yours.

398
00:24:50,458 --> 00:24:51,588
What you want to do.

399
00:24:52,188 --> 00:24:53,488
I...

400
00:24:54,758 --> 00:24:56,688
With Mom...

401
00:24:57,998 --> 00:24:59,358
I want to sleep next to her.

402
00:25:00,428 --> 00:25:02,928
I love that. Should we all
sleep in the same room?

403
00:25:03,468 --> 00:25:07,008
- No, I should stay out of it.
- What are you saying, Eun Bin?

404
00:25:07,368 --> 00:25:09,268
Let's all sleep next to each other,
the three of us. Okay?

405
00:25:09,668 --> 00:25:10,678
Really?

406
00:25:11,078 --> 00:25:13,848
Mom, that's okay with you, right?
Let's have a pajama party.

407
00:25:13,908 --> 00:25:17,678
Honey, let's do that after
I've talked it over with your dad.

408
00:25:17,918 --> 00:25:21,388
Because when your dad hears this,
things could get a little messy.

409
00:25:21,788 --> 00:25:23,918
Mom, can't we just
put it off for one day?

410
00:25:24,188 --> 00:25:25,188
What?

411
00:25:25,218 --> 00:25:30,028
Well, Dad's been in a bad mood.
What if he finds out and flips out?

412
00:25:30,128 --> 00:25:33,128
When I first found out who she was,
I totally panicked, too.

413
00:25:33,528 --> 00:25:34,898
I'm sorry, Eun Bin.

414
00:25:35,868 --> 00:25:38,468
You're right.
Okay, let's do that then.

415
00:25:39,738 --> 00:25:40,738
I'm home.

416
00:25:42,508 --> 00:25:45,008
- Dad!
- You're home.

417
00:25:45,638 --> 00:25:46,878
Yes.

418
00:25:48,008 --> 00:25:49,948
Come in. We need to talk.

419
00:25:50,048 --> 00:25:54,248
Dad, you can't!
We're having a girls' pajama party.

420
00:25:54,318 --> 00:25:56,118
What? What did you say?
What kind of party?

421
00:25:56,418 --> 00:25:59,918
Honey, can we talk tomorrow? Please.

422
00:26:18,908 --> 00:26:20,148
Did the talk go well?

423
00:26:21,348 --> 00:26:22,348
No.

424
00:26:23,048 --> 00:26:24,078
I couldn't do it.

425
00:26:24,718 --> 00:26:28,918
- Why not?
- The girls said a bazaar... No.

426
00:26:28,988 --> 00:26:30,618
They're having
some kind of pajama thing.

427
00:26:32,688 --> 00:26:36,358
Come to think of it,
I think Eun Bin already knew.

428
00:26:36,928 --> 00:26:40,098
She came to see me before and said
something very similar.

429
00:26:40,728 --> 00:26:41,828
That's what I was thinking.

430
00:26:43,198 --> 00:26:45,468
I was thinking about it on my walk,

431
00:26:46,198 --> 00:26:47,638
and I think this is
actually a good thing.

432
00:26:48,738 --> 00:26:51,378
Think about it, she's
our dear mom's actual daughter.

433
00:26:52,138 --> 00:26:54,648
She's the only real family
she has in the world.

434
00:26:55,408 --> 00:26:58,318
Imagine how happy she must be.
Right?

435
00:26:58,878 --> 00:27:01,218
And seeing how well
Eun Bin is handling it,

436
00:27:01,588 --> 00:27:04,618
it's probably because she hopes that
if she ever meets her birth mother,

437
00:27:04,718 --> 00:27:07,028
she'll be welcomed just as warmly.

438
00:27:07,088 --> 00:27:09,528
That may be why
she has accepted Min Seo.

439
00:27:16,968 --> 00:27:20,468
Hey, when did you two get
matching pajamas?

440
00:27:21,038 --> 00:27:25,238
Eun Bin gave them to me. She said
she wanted to do the sister thing.

441
00:27:26,278 --> 00:27:27,348
My goodness.

442
00:27:28,448 --> 00:27:29,908
You're so thoughtful, my dear.

443
00:27:30,978 --> 00:27:33,418
For some reason,
she didn't feel like a stranger.

444
00:27:34,418 --> 00:27:38,188
Let's do face masks, do our nails,
and take a bunch of pictures.

445
00:27:38,758 --> 00:27:41,158
Okay, let's do it. In that case,
what if I do something for my girls?

446
00:27:41,228 --> 00:27:43,128
Do your hair to go with
your new pajama-party look?

447
00:27:43,458 --> 00:27:46,058
Okay! Then Min Seo gets to go first.

448
00:27:46,798 --> 00:27:47,798
All right.

449
00:27:48,298 --> 00:27:52,338
Let's see. We've got
rollers, curlers, hairpins...

450
00:27:55,838 --> 00:27:58,308
We'll make it all poofy and curly,
like a grandma perm.

451
00:27:58,438 --> 00:28:00,178
The croissant look! A croissant!

452
00:28:01,078 --> 00:28:02,608
- Like a croissant.
- Yes, a croissant.

453
00:28:15,788 --> 00:28:18,498
What the... Why did I come here?

454
00:28:25,938 --> 00:28:27,408
- What?
- My gosh.

455
00:28:28,608 --> 00:28:31,108
Hello, Ms. Na.
I must've startled you.

456
00:28:31,308 --> 00:28:34,348
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to come here.

457
00:28:34,548 --> 00:28:38,278
I somehow ended up here.
I guess old habits die hard.

458
00:28:39,248 --> 00:28:40,318
Yes...

459
00:28:40,818 --> 00:28:42,388
I haven't said a word.

460
00:28:42,618 --> 00:28:46,558
Right. How's Dr. Han doing?

461
00:28:48,128 --> 00:28:49,728
She's doing well, thanks to you.

462
00:28:50,058 --> 00:28:53,628
I see.
Well, I'll be on my way, then.

463
00:28:54,968 --> 00:28:55,968
Director!

464
00:29:00,238 --> 00:29:02,208
What are you doing here?

465
00:29:02,668 --> 00:29:04,308
Tell me about it.

466
00:29:04,838 --> 00:29:07,278
Gosh, I totally forgot
that Ms. Gong and I broke up,

467
00:29:07,348 --> 00:29:09,378
and I instinctively walked here.
Can you believe it?

468
00:29:10,778 --> 00:29:12,048
Director...

469
00:29:12,448 --> 00:29:14,248
That's not exactly
something you just forget.

470
00:29:15,418 --> 00:29:18,358
I know, right?
Gosh, my head's not on straight.

471
00:29:18,988 --> 00:29:19,988
Oh, boy.

472
00:29:20,118 --> 00:29:23,558
This just won't do.
I'll remind you every morning.

473
00:29:23,758 --> 00:29:27,598
Yes, that sounds like a good plan.
Right. Well, then...

474
00:29:28,468 --> 00:29:31,498
- Well, I'll see you tomorrow.
- Okay.

475
00:29:31,838 --> 00:29:32,838
All right, take care.

476
00:29:40,408 --> 00:29:41,648
Grandma, let's go in.

477
00:29:52,788 --> 00:29:53,928
I'm home.

478
00:29:54,188 --> 00:29:55,358
You're back?

479
00:29:55,628 --> 00:29:56,958
Mom, how are you feeling?

480
00:29:57,698 --> 00:29:59,128
You asked me
like a dozen times on the phone,

481
00:29:59,128 --> 00:30:00,198
and you're asking again?

482
00:30:00,628 --> 00:30:02,298
I'm feeling much better.

483
00:30:02,498 --> 00:30:05,698
Still.
You really can't push yourself yet.

484
00:30:05,768 --> 00:30:07,408
As if I don't know that.

485
00:30:07,538 --> 00:30:09,808
I'll be checking on you every day,
just so you know.

486
00:30:10,578 --> 00:30:11,738
Such a nag.

487
00:30:12,138 --> 00:30:14,778
Hurry upstairs, get changed,
and have some dinner.

488
00:30:14,848 --> 00:30:16,278
Okay, I will.

489
00:30:19,248 --> 00:30:20,788
Why is she being so dramatic?

490
00:30:22,318 --> 00:30:23,958
She's coping.

491
00:30:25,688 --> 00:30:28,328
The fallout from her breakup
with Jun Hyeok?

492
00:30:30,228 --> 00:30:32,728
Jun Hyeok was just a cover.

493
00:30:33,698 --> 00:30:34,698
What?

494
00:30:35,498 --> 00:30:37,838
The one Ju Ah was dating
and broke up with...

495
00:30:38,168 --> 00:30:40,408
wasn't Jun Hyeok.
It was Director Yang.

496
00:30:43,238 --> 00:30:44,238
You're not surprised?

497
00:30:45,338 --> 00:30:47,908
Well, I had a feeling
that might be the case.

498
00:30:49,048 --> 00:30:51,918
So is Director Yang quitting
and leaving...

499
00:30:52,248 --> 00:30:53,518
because of that?

500
00:30:54,248 --> 00:30:56,048
More or less.

501
00:30:57,118 --> 00:30:58,758
Ju Ah must have had
a really hard time.

502
00:30:59,618 --> 00:31:00,728
Tell me about it.

503
00:31:03,228 --> 00:31:04,258
Mother.

504
00:31:05,628 --> 00:31:07,268
Are you sad it didn't work out
with Director Yang?

505
00:31:08,798 --> 00:31:10,838
Well, even if I were,
what could I do about it?

506
00:31:11,498 --> 00:31:13,668
It was never going to work out
between them anyway.

507
00:31:14,508 --> 00:31:15,608
Exactly.

508
00:31:17,678 --> 00:31:18,978
Besides, Father is...

509
00:31:19,308 --> 00:31:22,348
probably living happily
with Bucket's mom.

510
00:31:24,248 --> 00:31:26,048
Well, they knew it too,

511
00:31:26,418 --> 00:31:27,888
which is why
they broke up on their own.

512
00:31:28,548 --> 00:31:30,788
Let's just pretend
we don't know anything.

513
00:31:35,988 --> 00:31:39,228
If you think about it,
it's a weird relationship, Uncle.

514
00:31:40,968 --> 00:31:44,038
I know. But what can I do?
The heart wants what it wants.

515
00:31:45,668 --> 00:31:48,438
Yes, I think I know how you feel.

516
00:31:49,208 --> 00:31:50,338
Thanks for getting it.

517
00:31:52,078 --> 00:31:53,578
So, what are you going to do now?

518
00:31:53,978 --> 00:31:56,278
Now that Dad knows, it won't be long
before you're found out.

519
00:31:57,318 --> 00:31:58,578
Man, I don't know.

520
00:31:59,548 --> 00:32:01,518
My brother refuses
to even hear me out.

521
00:32:02,748 --> 00:32:05,558
In that case,
why don't you try talking to Mom?

522
00:32:05,758 --> 00:32:10,128
What? Hey, your dad will kill me.
Especially since your mom is sick.

523
00:32:10,358 --> 00:32:11,828
I'm sure Mom will be fine.

524
00:32:12,358 --> 00:32:13,968
She'd be more upset
if you kept it from her.

525
00:32:14,998 --> 00:32:18,898
- You think so?
- Yes. Remember the fake video?

526
00:32:18,998 --> 00:32:20,938
We hid it from her,
and it got worse.

527
00:32:20,938 --> 00:32:23,008
Mom had to fix it all in the end.

528
00:32:25,678 --> 00:32:26,708
Do you think
she'll give her blessing?

529
00:32:27,778 --> 00:32:30,248
I think that's a whole other issue,
though.

530
00:32:32,248 --> 00:32:35,018
Don't sneak around and break up.
You need to take this head-on.

531
00:32:35,348 --> 00:32:38,058
You're not one to give up
before trying, are you, Uncle?

532
00:32:40,418 --> 00:32:41,488
You're right.

533
00:32:42,028 --> 00:32:43,058
You little punk.

534
00:32:44,458 --> 00:32:45,928
You really get your uncle,
don't you?

535
00:32:58,508 --> 00:32:59,538
Done with work?

536
00:33:01,348 --> 00:33:02,908
Just drink and go to bed.

537
00:33:03,308 --> 00:33:05,978
Don't be stupid and call him
to ask to get back together.

538
00:33:06,518 --> 00:33:07,848
That's not going to happen.

539
00:33:09,788 --> 00:33:12,458
So, about our uncle's girlfriend...

540
00:33:13,758 --> 00:33:14,858
She's Hyun Bin's aunt.

541
00:33:15,888 --> 00:33:16,888
What?

542
00:33:18,058 --> 00:33:21,768
Wait, how is that even possible?

543
00:33:22,268 --> 00:33:24,798
I don't know. But anyway,
that's what happened.

544
00:33:25,368 --> 00:33:26,798
It looks like
he's not going to give up.

545
00:33:27,068 --> 00:33:29,508
Dad already found out,
and he'll probably tell Mom soon.

546
00:33:30,138 --> 00:33:32,708
Grandma's going to hate this.

547
00:33:33,638 --> 00:33:34,678
Tell me about it.

548
00:33:36,378 --> 00:33:39,278
But if, despite all that,
he manages to get their approval,

549
00:33:39,778 --> 00:33:41,988
then you can't be with Hyun Bin.
You get that, right?

550
00:33:42,288 --> 00:33:45,288
It's already over.
Don't worry. Just go to your room.

551
00:33:59,468 --> 00:34:01,008
Oh, you do this for me, too?

552
00:34:01,668 --> 00:34:06,278
Of course. For the VIP of the house?
This kind of service is a given.

553
00:34:08,048 --> 00:34:09,048
By the way,

554
00:34:09,548 --> 00:34:11,818
I'm going to the hospital
with your brother.

555
00:34:12,678 --> 00:34:14,588
Why? I'll take you.

556
00:34:15,118 --> 00:34:18,558
He said you were busy,
so he cleared his schedule for me.

557
00:34:19,288 --> 00:34:20,588
Gosh, that guy.

558
00:34:20,888 --> 00:34:22,158
What's wrong?

559
00:34:22,588 --> 00:34:25,828
You should thank him.
You won't find a brother like him.

560
00:34:27,028 --> 00:34:29,828
Yes, you're right.
Should I get the lights?

561
00:34:30,098 --> 00:34:32,598
- Yes.
- Okay, easy now. Careful.

562
00:34:32,668 --> 00:34:33,668
Okay.

563
00:35:33,958 --> 00:35:34,998
Mom, are you not feeling well?

564
00:35:36,128 --> 00:35:38,438
About me seeing Mr. Gong...

565
00:35:39,138 --> 00:35:40,838
His family found out we're dating.

566
00:35:42,038 --> 00:35:43,238
Who in his family?

567
00:35:43,908 --> 00:35:44,908
Dr. Gong.

568
00:35:45,578 --> 00:35:46,908
Oh, that's the worst.

569
00:35:47,878 --> 00:35:49,908
That means
Uncle could find out right away.

570
00:35:52,278 --> 00:35:53,278
I'm sure he will.

571
00:35:54,088 --> 00:35:56,748
If Uncle finds out,
he might actually hit Mr. Gong.

572
00:35:59,188 --> 00:36:01,788
What? He wouldn't do that.

573
00:36:02,328 --> 00:36:03,458
Uncle...

574
00:36:03,928 --> 00:36:06,628
When it comes to family,
he always leads with his emotions.

575
00:36:07,468 --> 00:36:09,298
Remember that time
he tracked down Dad and hit him?

576
00:36:09,628 --> 00:36:10,628
Don't you remember?

577
00:36:17,068 --> 00:36:19,138
Ju Ah,
I hear you have an interview today.

578
00:36:19,578 --> 00:36:22,378
Yes, an exclusive interview
with a fashion magazine.

579
00:36:23,678 --> 00:36:25,548
- Wow, really?
- Yes.

580
00:36:25,818 --> 00:36:28,448
It'll be released on the magazine's
YouTube channel first.

581
00:36:29,048 --> 00:36:32,618
And I got a scouting offer
from another brand.

582
00:36:34,358 --> 00:36:37,698
- So what, are you going to take it?
- Are you crazy?

583
00:36:38,628 --> 00:36:43,128
They were impressed by the show
and want me to handle their line.

584
00:36:43,198 --> 00:36:44,438
I'm just bragging.

585
00:36:44,738 --> 00:36:46,668
Hey, during your interview today,

586
00:36:46,968 --> 00:36:48,638
make sure
you brag a lot about your mom.

587
00:36:48,738 --> 00:36:51,578
Oh, of course.
It's all thanks to Mom.

588
00:36:52,508 --> 00:36:53,938
Thank you, sweetheart.

589
00:36:55,108 --> 00:36:58,048
Hey, Seong Mi. Today, we'll begin
some gentle joint exercises.

590
00:36:58,918 --> 00:36:59,978
Okay.

591
00:37:01,288 --> 00:37:03,718
So you're giving her
personalized physical therapy?

592
00:37:04,118 --> 00:37:08,288
Yes, she needs to stretch regularly
to prevent shoulder and chest pain.

593
00:37:09,758 --> 00:37:10,758
Dae Han.

594
00:37:11,058 --> 00:37:13,498
By the way, who were you eating
dumplings with yesterday?

595
00:37:14,868 --> 00:37:15,868
What?

596
00:37:15,928 --> 00:37:19,768
I heard you were out with your girl
yesterday. Does she live near here?

597
00:37:20,138 --> 00:37:21,138
Who is she?

598
00:37:22,908 --> 00:37:24,538
Well...

599
00:37:28,108 --> 00:37:29,108
Later.

600
00:37:30,678 --> 00:37:31,948
I'll tell you all later.

601
00:37:32,278 --> 00:37:34,948
The suspense is killing me.

602
00:37:42,628 --> 00:37:45,058
(Taehan)

603
00:37:45,458 --> 00:37:46,698
- Ms. Shin.
- Yes.

604
00:37:48,698 --> 00:37:52,468
- If you cinch it here...
- Right, cinch it for some volume...

605
00:38:00,008 --> 00:38:01,948
(Fantom Sports)

606
00:38:08,018 --> 00:38:10,018
Hey, why are you taking
my picture without asking?

607
00:38:12,458 --> 00:38:14,088
There. If I do this...

608
00:38:14,558 --> 00:38:18,198
- I don't need your permission.
- Gosh, why are you taking pictures?

609
00:38:19,428 --> 00:38:21,428
So I can look at them
whenever I miss you guys.

610
00:38:21,828 --> 00:38:22,828
My team.

611
00:38:26,898 --> 00:38:29,568
If you're going to be like this,
then just don't go, okay?

612
00:38:29,868 --> 00:38:33,738
My mind's made up, so accept it.
I already bought my plane ticket.

613
00:38:36,408 --> 00:38:39,048
All right, let's head to
the store concept meeting.

614
00:38:39,348 --> 00:38:40,378
Ms. Gong.

615
00:38:41,418 --> 00:38:44,048
Oh, look at the time.

616
00:38:44,788 --> 00:38:47,688
Hey, want me to go instead
if it's awkward for you two?

617
00:38:48,288 --> 00:38:50,758
Awkward? It's part of my job.

618
00:38:51,158 --> 00:38:52,328
We're not awkward.

619
00:39:02,708 --> 00:39:04,168
Oh, boy.

620
00:39:05,238 --> 00:39:06,338
Right?

621
00:39:06,938 --> 00:39:07,948
Tell me about it.

622
00:39:08,378 --> 00:39:09,608
I guess
we're the only sad ones here.

623
00:39:13,778 --> 00:39:14,918
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

624
00:39:14,988 --> 00:39:16,018
Mr. Gong.

625
00:39:16,888 --> 00:39:18,818
I was looking at
Mr. Park Seong Woo's chart,

626
00:39:19,218 --> 00:39:21,728
and why's his knee's range of motion
so inconsistent?

627
00:39:22,458 --> 00:39:26,698
With chronic inflammation, his pain
varies with weather or activity...

628
00:39:26,758 --> 00:39:30,098
Didn't his condition worsen because
you increased the therapy intensity?

629
00:39:30,428 --> 00:39:33,668
Hey, are you saying
my methods are the problem?

630
00:39:33,898 --> 00:39:35,638
I'm not saying it's a problem.

631
00:39:36,438 --> 00:39:38,278
It's just not having any effect,
so...

632
00:39:38,278 --> 00:39:41,378
I ran everything by you beforehand.
Why are you bringing this up now?

633
00:39:41,478 --> 00:39:44,208
What, so you're saying
I'm just nitpicking for no reason?

634
00:39:44,448 --> 00:39:48,888
- Honestly? Yes.
- Come on. Why are you like this?

635
00:39:48,988 --> 00:39:51,188
I was really trying
to put up with it, but...

636
00:39:51,318 --> 00:39:54,218
Hey! What have you put up with?
What could you have to put up with?

637
00:39:54,288 --> 00:39:57,228
Let's keep this professional.
Why are you getting personal?

638
00:39:57,288 --> 00:40:00,258
Who's getting personal?
You didn't do your part.

639
00:40:00,328 --> 00:40:03,168
What are you guys doing?
There are patients here.

640
00:40:04,168 --> 00:40:05,168
What?

641
00:40:06,698 --> 00:40:07,738
Why, that...

642
00:40:09,138 --> 00:40:11,708
Hey. What's going on?

643
00:40:12,908 --> 00:40:15,678
No, it's... It's nothing. Really.

644
00:40:25,618 --> 00:40:27,788
Dr. Gong found out
about you two, didn't he?

645
00:40:28,428 --> 00:40:30,288
Yes. While we were eating dumplings.

646
00:40:30,928 --> 00:40:33,258
Well, I knew this day would come.

647
00:40:34,198 --> 00:40:36,598
How much does he know?
Who else knows?

648
00:40:36,968 --> 00:40:37,968
Just my brother, for now.

649
00:40:39,498 --> 00:40:41,568
I'm worried about what will happen
if Dr. Yang finds out.

650
00:40:43,038 --> 00:40:44,038
Man...

651
00:40:46,008 --> 00:40:47,908
(Mustard leaf kimchi for sale)

652
00:40:51,918 --> 00:40:53,978
(Seafood trio)

653
00:41:01,758 --> 00:41:06,458
Jin Ah. Are you mad at me because...

654
00:41:06,758 --> 00:41:07,768
I canceled our movie date?

655
00:41:08,368 --> 00:41:12,438
- Yes.
- So Mr. Gong was right.

656
00:41:12,698 --> 00:41:14,338
So you were upset.

657
00:41:14,838 --> 00:41:16,108
Did I really have to
spell that out for you?

658
00:41:16,708 --> 00:41:17,808
Well, yes.

659
00:41:18,408 --> 00:41:19,678
You know
this is my first relationship.

660
00:41:20,208 --> 00:41:21,208
There's still a lot I don't know.

661
00:41:22,348 --> 00:41:24,208
Right. I'll keep that in mind.

662
00:41:24,548 --> 00:41:27,148
I'd already figured out
that you're hopelessly clueless.

663
00:41:28,188 --> 00:41:32,688
If I'm lacking, please tell me.
I'll correct it immediately.

664
00:41:33,788 --> 00:41:35,788
It took a lot for me
to make this decision.

665
00:41:37,458 --> 00:41:38,558
I will do my absolute best.

666
00:41:41,298 --> 00:41:42,298
My gosh.

667
00:41:43,028 --> 00:41:44,028
That's actually really cute.

668
00:41:44,538 --> 00:41:45,538
What?

669
00:41:46,098 --> 00:41:49,438
Does that mean you think
I'm genuinely cute?

670
00:41:49,808 --> 00:41:51,808
Yes. You are.

671
00:41:54,478 --> 00:41:55,648
So cute!

672
00:41:59,118 --> 00:42:00,448
Can you do this side, too?

673
00:42:02,088 --> 00:42:04,188
That's enough. Let's eat.

674
00:42:04,558 --> 00:42:06,388
Right. Okay.

675
00:42:08,188 --> 00:42:09,188
My gosh.

676
00:42:13,028 --> 00:42:16,768
The store's concept is really good,
don't you think?

677
00:42:17,068 --> 00:42:19,868
Yes, I think it reflects
the brand's story very well.

678
00:42:21,368 --> 00:42:23,438
Director, are you heading back
to the office?

679
00:42:24,608 --> 00:42:28,948
Well, yes.
You have that interview, right?

680
00:42:30,248 --> 00:42:32,218
I still have a little time.

681
00:42:34,688 --> 00:42:36,648
Would you like to grab
a bite to eat?

682
00:42:37,518 --> 00:42:38,718
Should we?

683
00:42:39,288 --> 00:42:40,788
That should be okay, right?

684
00:42:42,088 --> 00:42:43,428
What are you in the mood for?

685
00:42:45,698 --> 00:42:48,628
There's something I haven't had yet
since coming back to Korea.

686
00:42:50,168 --> 00:42:51,268
Okay.

687
00:43:02,478 --> 00:43:03,478
Wow.

688
00:43:06,078 --> 00:43:09,218
If I'd gone back without this,
I would've regretted it.

689
00:43:09,988 --> 00:43:14,258
Before you go, eat what you want
and do whatever you want.

690
00:43:14,728 --> 00:43:17,588
If you don't have anyone to go with,
I can join you.

691
00:43:19,428 --> 00:43:20,458
Maybe we would've been okay...

692
00:43:21,298 --> 00:43:23,928
if we'd just stayed friends
like this.

693
00:43:24,368 --> 00:43:25,368
Right?

694
00:43:26,868 --> 00:43:28,008
I wouldn't have been.

695
00:43:31,538 --> 00:43:32,578
Right now...

696
00:43:33,438 --> 00:43:34,948
I'm just enduring it.

697
00:43:36,948 --> 00:43:38,618
Oh, come on.

698
00:43:39,878 --> 00:43:41,548
Don't make this so hard on yourself.

699
00:43:43,218 --> 00:43:45,758
Okay. I'll try.

700
00:43:48,688 --> 00:43:50,588
- Director.
- Yes.

701
00:43:50,788 --> 00:43:55,368
Apparently, my uncle
and your aunt are dating.

702
00:43:55,828 --> 00:43:56,828
Yes. Wait, what?

703
00:43:57,528 --> 00:43:58,538
For real?

704
00:43:59,168 --> 00:44:00,268
Yes.

705
00:44:00,638 --> 00:44:02,108
Wow, this is...

706
00:44:02,768 --> 00:44:04,908
like something
straight out of a movie.

707
00:44:05,008 --> 00:44:09,078
They were secretly dating like us,
and my dad found out.

708
00:44:10,478 --> 00:44:13,348
Man, my father's going to flip out
if he finds out.

709
00:44:13,648 --> 00:44:14,648
Tell me about it.

710
00:44:14,918 --> 00:44:17,548
Getting their parents' blessing
won't be easy for them either.

711
00:44:19,718 --> 00:44:22,258
The more I hear about it,
the more it feels like...

712
00:44:23,128 --> 00:44:24,758
we were never meant to be.

713
00:44:26,898 --> 00:44:27,898
I guess so.

714
00:44:28,298 --> 00:44:29,928
It's probably for the best
that we ended things.

715
00:44:35,838 --> 00:44:37,238
It's not hard for you at all?

716
00:44:37,838 --> 00:44:38,838
Really?

717
00:44:44,508 --> 00:44:47,018
Honestly,

718
00:44:47,818 --> 00:44:49,948
it's more bearable than I expected.

719
00:44:52,218 --> 00:44:53,218
That's a relief.

720
00:45:08,038 --> 00:45:09,168
I'll start us off, then.

721
00:45:09,638 --> 00:45:11,538
- Hello.
- Yes, hello.

722
00:45:12,538 --> 00:45:17,148
In the show's opening, you said
you're a "Fashion Therapist."

723
00:45:17,508 --> 00:45:20,248
Is there a particular reason
you chose that title?

724
00:45:20,818 --> 00:45:24,588
That's how my mother defined
what a designer is.

725
00:45:25,188 --> 00:45:27,918
She said,
by making clothes that suit people,

726
00:45:28,058 --> 00:45:30,788
a designer becomes a healer
who mends their spirit.

727
00:45:31,058 --> 00:45:34,558
I see. So that's why, to go with
your collection's message,

728
00:45:34,768 --> 00:45:37,528
you featured Dr. Han Seong Mi
as your main model.

729
00:45:37,828 --> 00:45:38,938
Yes.

730
00:45:40,398 --> 00:45:41,408
Actually,

731
00:45:42,408 --> 00:45:47,238
my mother who told me that
is Dr. Han Seong Mi.

732
00:45:47,578 --> 00:45:49,148
What? Really?

733
00:45:52,078 --> 00:45:56,388
Wow. For your mom to walk the runway
wearing the clothes you designed...

734
00:45:56,888 --> 00:46:01,528
- Wow, that must've been so special.
- My lifelong dream came true.

735
00:46:03,388 --> 00:46:06,128
The show's concept
was both modern...

736
00:46:06,198 --> 00:46:08,628
and luxurious,
which I found very impressive.

737
00:46:08,998 --> 00:46:13,098
Was there anyone in particular
who inspired this collection?

738
00:46:13,538 --> 00:46:15,908
Someone who inspired me?

739
00:46:19,278 --> 00:46:20,378
You know,

740
00:46:20,938 --> 00:46:25,178
I love seeing people happy
in the clothes I make.

741
00:46:25,848 --> 00:46:26,848
I love making people happy.

742
00:46:27,948 --> 00:46:28,948
That's admirable.

743
00:46:29,948 --> 00:46:32,758
Someone who creates happiness.

744
00:46:33,458 --> 00:46:36,288
Moving forward, I'll listen to you,
and we'll face challenges together,

745
00:46:36,628 --> 00:46:40,298
so the people wearing your clothes
can be happy.

746
00:46:40,958 --> 00:46:43,368
I'll be right there with you,
working through it all,

747
00:46:44,198 --> 00:46:45,298
and helping in any way I can.

748
00:46:45,298 --> 00:46:46,898
Your mother wearing your designs...

749
00:46:46,968 --> 00:46:49,408
and walking the opening runway,

750
00:46:49,768 --> 00:46:53,108
and you two bowing at the finale...
I think that would be wonderful.

751
00:47:03,818 --> 00:47:07,588
And may I ask who that person is?

752
00:47:09,058 --> 00:47:10,688
That person is...

753
00:47:12,058 --> 00:47:13,058
He's...

754
00:47:13,758 --> 00:47:16,568
the one who made it possible for me
to become a designer.

755
00:47:17,598 --> 00:47:19,368
The one who created
my entire world...

756
00:47:20,568 --> 00:47:21,568
I'm sorry.

757
00:47:24,168 --> 00:47:27,138
All right.
Should we take a little break?

758
00:47:28,008 --> 00:47:29,008
Yes.

759
00:48:16,988 --> 00:48:20,158
(Korean Medicine Doctor
Yang Dong Ik)

760
00:48:20,258 --> 00:48:21,258
The Private Detective Agency.

761
00:48:25,568 --> 00:48:28,438
Right, I totally forgot I asked you
to look into other things.

762
00:48:30,468 --> 00:48:31,478
About that...

763
00:48:32,008 --> 00:48:33,378
You can drop the case.

764
00:48:34,178 --> 00:48:35,578
So, should I get rid of all this?

765
00:48:36,548 --> 00:48:37,748
What do you mean?

766
00:48:38,478 --> 00:48:39,748
What did you find?

767
00:48:40,448 --> 00:48:43,088
Your wife visited a travel agency
and also met with a lawyer.

768
00:48:44,648 --> 00:48:45,758
She did?

769
00:48:48,888 --> 00:48:49,888
See for yourself.

770
00:48:57,898 --> 00:49:00,498
(Civil, Criminal, Divorce)

771
00:49:01,068 --> 00:49:02,068
(Couples Tour)

772
00:49:06,938 --> 00:49:10,608
She's paid and with her daughter,
so she's settling her finances...

773
00:49:10,708 --> 00:49:12,218
and booking a flight.

774
00:49:12,818 --> 00:49:14,048
The writing's on the wall.

775
00:49:19,558 --> 00:49:20,588
(Application for Divorce
by Mutual Consent)

776
00:49:21,088 --> 00:49:23,988
If you want to file for divorce,
I can get you more evidence.

777
00:49:24,328 --> 00:49:25,698
Better catch her
before she skips town.

778
00:49:31,668 --> 00:49:34,238
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

779
00:49:38,168 --> 00:49:41,948
- Have you heard from Se Ri?
- No. Why? What about Se Ri?

780
00:49:42,578 --> 00:49:43,708
She said she has something to say...

781
00:49:43,708 --> 00:49:46,448
and told us to be prepared
and come together.

782
00:49:47,448 --> 00:49:48,518
She did?

783
00:49:48,818 --> 00:49:52,018
I'm curious. My appointment's over,
so I'll go on ahead.

784
00:49:52,418 --> 00:49:55,188
Okay, I'll see my scheduled patients
and then I'll head over.

785
00:50:05,998 --> 00:50:07,198
Hey, Hyun Bin.

786
00:50:07,868 --> 00:50:09,308
I'm heading down there today, too.

787
00:50:09,908 --> 00:50:10,908
Why?

788
00:50:11,208 --> 00:50:14,008
Mother said to come over. She said
she has something to tell everyone.

789
00:50:14,638 --> 00:50:19,118
- She did?
- Yes. It seems she'll tell us all.

790
00:50:19,378 --> 00:50:22,048
Also, I asked Eun Bin
just to be sure,

791
00:50:23,388 --> 00:50:26,388
and it turns out
she knew everything all along.

792
00:50:28,358 --> 00:50:29,358
Really?

793
00:50:29,528 --> 00:50:33,828
She said Mother didn't secretly
bring Min Seo home behind your back.

794
00:50:34,058 --> 00:50:36,798
It was a complete coincidence
she ended up there.

795
00:50:37,928 --> 00:50:39,138
Are you absolutely sure?

796
00:50:39,538 --> 00:50:43,508
You'll hear the whole story later.
And don't get worked up, all right?

797
00:50:47,508 --> 00:50:48,508
Then...

798
00:50:49,008 --> 00:50:50,748
Why did she meet with a lawyer?

799
00:50:52,778 --> 00:50:53,848
Where's my medicine?

800
00:51:00,088 --> 00:51:01,318
There must be a reason.

801
00:51:02,428 --> 00:51:03,428
Right.

802
00:51:03,958 --> 00:51:05,128
I trust Se Ri.

803
00:51:06,098 --> 00:51:07,128
I have to trust her.

804
00:51:14,098 --> 00:51:16,008
These lentils are great in the rice.

805
00:51:16,908 --> 00:51:18,268
Dae Han bought them.

806
00:51:19,138 --> 00:51:22,678
I heard you were feeling nauseous.
These are easy to digest.

807
00:51:22,948 --> 00:51:25,178
They're rich in protein and folate,
so they're really good for you.

808
00:51:26,318 --> 00:51:30,288
So thoughtful of you, Dae Han.
It really hits the spot.

809
00:51:31,518 --> 00:51:33,918
Did you apologize to your brother?

810
00:51:36,158 --> 00:51:37,158
Why should I?

811
00:51:37,428 --> 00:51:38,698
What do you mean, "Why?"

812
00:51:39,398 --> 00:51:41,598
Don't talk to your brother that way,
not with patients around.

813
00:51:42,428 --> 00:51:45,598
Mom, you don't know the whole story.
Why are you only blaming me?

814
00:51:46,238 --> 00:51:48,408
- What?
- Why am I always the one...

815
00:51:49,008 --> 00:51:51,778
who has to apologize, endure it,
and give in? Why?

816
00:51:52,308 --> 00:51:53,678
That really hurts, Mom.

817
00:51:54,338 --> 00:51:55,348
Good grief.

818
00:51:56,978 --> 00:51:58,048
I can't believe him.

819
00:52:03,318 --> 00:52:05,518
- Dae Han.
- Yes?

820
00:52:07,588 --> 00:52:08,588
Yes.

821
00:52:14,158 --> 00:52:15,328
I'm sorry.

822
00:52:15,828 --> 00:52:17,568
I let my emotions
get the better of me.

823
00:52:19,798 --> 00:52:21,868
Why don't you calmly tell me
what happened from the start?

824
00:52:22,968 --> 00:52:24,408
Why did you and your brother fight?

825
00:52:25,278 --> 00:52:28,238
I can't tell you.
Jeong Han will be angry if I do.

826
00:52:28,708 --> 00:52:30,108
Don't worry about that.

827
00:52:30,108 --> 00:52:32,448
Just pretend
you're talking to a doctor...

828
00:52:32,518 --> 00:52:34,018
and tell me what's on your mind.

829
00:52:34,678 --> 00:52:36,718
It might shock you,
and that would cause you stress.

830
00:52:37,318 --> 00:52:42,158
Trust me, I've heard everything.
It takes a lot to shock me.

831
00:52:42,888 --> 00:52:44,688
Go on, tell me.
Why did you two fight?

832
00:52:48,058 --> 00:52:49,068
It's Dong Suk.

833
00:52:50,068 --> 00:52:52,338
- I'm sorry?
- My girlfriend.

834
00:52:53,398 --> 00:52:54,398
It's Dong Suk.

835
00:52:56,538 --> 00:52:59,908
Bucket's sister, Yang Dong Suk?

836
00:53:00,738 --> 00:53:01,808
Yes.

837
00:53:04,608 --> 00:53:06,648
I thought you said
you wouldn't be shocked.

838
00:53:07,278 --> 00:53:09,688
Right, I'm sorry.

839
00:53:12,088 --> 00:53:13,358
You see...

840
00:53:14,688 --> 00:53:16,388
When Hui Gyeong and I broke up,

841
00:53:16,988 --> 00:53:19,458
I thought I'd never be able
to love again. But...

842
00:53:19,728 --> 00:53:21,558
after I met Dong Suk,
I realized something.

843
00:53:22,028 --> 00:53:24,398
What I thought was love before
wasn't real love.

844
00:53:25,638 --> 00:53:29,238
Dong Suk is like
my missing puzzle piece.

845
00:53:29,538 --> 00:53:31,338
You know when you've put almost
the whole thing together,

846
00:53:31,438 --> 00:53:34,608
but feel so empty because
that very last piece is missing?

847
00:53:35,748 --> 00:53:36,748
I do.

848
00:53:37,508 --> 00:53:39,448
She's that final piece for me.

849
00:53:40,918 --> 00:53:43,018
She's someone who has everything
I could ever want,

850
00:53:44,288 --> 00:53:47,018
and still gives everything she has.
That's the kind of person she is.

851
00:53:48,658 --> 00:53:50,388
To find someone like that
in your life...

852
00:53:52,528 --> 00:53:54,328
It's a miracle, isn't it?

853
00:53:56,028 --> 00:53:57,028
It is.

854
00:53:57,528 --> 00:53:58,838
I'm so sorry.

855
00:53:59,868 --> 00:54:02,968
I know I shouldn't be saying this,
but I just can't control my heart.

856
00:54:03,838 --> 00:54:05,108
Don't be sorry.

857
00:54:06,408 --> 00:54:07,508
I am sorry.

858
00:54:22,528 --> 00:54:24,328
- You're home.
- Yes.

859
00:54:25,358 --> 00:54:26,728
I see Eun Bin and Dong Suk
are here, too.

860
00:54:27,728 --> 00:54:28,828
Who's watching the stores?

861
00:54:29,598 --> 00:54:33,498
Min Seo's watching my store,
and I sent Eun Bin to Dong Suk's.

862
00:54:34,338 --> 00:54:36,308
What's this all about?
You're making it sound so serious.

863
00:54:37,408 --> 00:54:40,578
There's something
I need to tell everyone.

864
00:54:41,438 --> 00:54:44,378
I'll wait for you outside,
so go get changed and come on out.

865
00:54:59,198 --> 00:55:01,298
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

866
00:55:03,828 --> 00:55:04,898
Enjoy your meal.

867
00:55:06,538 --> 00:55:09,308
Okay, and the table over there...

868
00:55:10,108 --> 00:55:11,238
Enjoy.

869
00:55:15,038 --> 00:55:16,708
I'll get you some more side dishes.

870
00:55:17,078 --> 00:55:19,718
- Here you go. Enjoy your meal.
- Enjoy your meal.

871
00:55:28,658 --> 00:55:29,658
Eun Bin.

872
00:55:32,128 --> 00:55:33,128
Yes?

873
00:55:34,828 --> 00:55:36,198
It's been a while.

874
00:55:38,398 --> 00:55:39,398
Yes, it has.

875
00:55:54,618 --> 00:55:55,618
I'm sorry.

876
00:55:56,548 --> 00:55:58,188
For not telling you all sooner.

877
00:55:58,818 --> 00:55:59,818
So, wait.

878
00:56:00,418 --> 00:56:03,258
So, you're saying
Min Seo is your daughter?

879
00:56:04,958 --> 00:56:07,398
Isn't it a crazy coincidence?

880
00:56:08,328 --> 00:56:10,498
Apparently, they didn't even have
each other's contact info.

881
00:56:11,068 --> 00:56:16,008
I guess so. But what are the odds
she'd end up in Onjeong?

882
00:56:16,908 --> 00:56:19,478
She was on a nationwide tour
of the best tteokbokki spots.

883
00:56:19,738 --> 00:56:22,908
Then she got her bag stolen
in Onjeong and ended up staying.

884
00:56:23,948 --> 00:56:24,948
I'll tell you what.

885
00:56:27,648 --> 00:56:28,988
From the moment I first saw her,

886
00:56:29,688 --> 00:56:30,888
I just had this feeling.

887
00:56:31,718 --> 00:56:32,718
That's right!

888
00:56:32,958 --> 00:56:36,488
Dad, you did say she looked familiar
the first time you saw her.

889
00:56:39,098 --> 00:56:40,658
I'm sorry, honey.

890
00:56:41,828 --> 00:56:44,828
I never should have hidden
my past from you.

891
00:56:50,168 --> 00:56:55,138
Well, you knew how our family feels
about mothers abandoning their kids.

892
00:56:56,348 --> 00:56:57,708
So it must have been hard for you
to say anything.

893
00:57:00,578 --> 00:57:01,778
Even if I'd known,

894
00:57:03,088 --> 00:57:04,518
I still would have married you.

895
00:57:06,218 --> 00:57:07,258
Honey...

896
00:57:09,188 --> 00:57:10,358
But Se Ri,

897
00:57:11,058 --> 00:57:13,128
it must have been so hard for you
to give her up.

898
00:57:13,528 --> 00:57:15,698
Especially when she turned one.
They're so adorable at that age.

899
00:57:18,328 --> 00:57:20,798
It's such a blessing
you could be reunited.

900
00:57:22,638 --> 00:57:23,638
It really is.

901
00:57:24,038 --> 00:57:26,308
Wait, Hyun Bin,
how did you know all this?

902
00:57:27,808 --> 00:57:31,708
Eun Bin told me.
She was the first one to find out.

903
00:57:31,808 --> 00:57:33,978
My gosh. Eun Bin's really grown up.

904
00:57:34,348 --> 00:57:36,648
To think she accepted it all
without making a scene.

905
00:57:38,248 --> 00:57:40,718
That's all a credit to Se Ri
for raising her so well.

906
00:57:41,888 --> 00:57:43,488
You've earned this blessing.

907
00:57:44,288 --> 00:57:48,898
So that's why she felt so familiar.
This is wonderful.

908
00:57:49,598 --> 00:57:51,098
Tell her to stay a while longer,
Dong Ik.

909
00:57:52,768 --> 00:57:53,798
She's right, Se Ri.

910
00:57:54,238 --> 00:57:55,408
Have her stay with you
a little longer.

911
00:57:57,038 --> 00:57:58,038
Really?

912
00:57:59,038 --> 00:58:00,678
Are you sure that's okay?

913
00:58:23,498 --> 00:58:24,998
I'm sorry.

914
00:58:28,098 --> 00:58:30,238
I hate to say this, but...

915
00:58:31,268 --> 00:58:32,578
my brother, Dae Han...

916
00:58:33,238 --> 00:58:35,948
He's so naive,
he doesn't know which way is up.

917
00:58:37,378 --> 00:58:38,378
Dong Suk.

918
00:58:39,518 --> 00:58:41,178
I know this is a lot to ask,

919
00:58:42,318 --> 00:58:44,388
but instead of just thinking
about your feelings for each other,

920
00:58:45,558 --> 00:58:48,518
could you please try to consider
how this affects everyone else?

921
00:58:53,528 --> 00:58:54,728
People like your brother and me.

922
00:58:56,128 --> 00:58:58,598
You know we searched everywhere
for your mother and my father.

923
00:58:59,838 --> 00:59:00,838
Yes.

924
00:59:02,038 --> 00:59:03,038
But...

925
00:59:03,968 --> 00:59:05,678
do you know why
we're not looking for them anymore?

926
00:59:07,178 --> 00:59:10,948
I heard our parents told you not to.

927
00:59:11,708 --> 00:59:12,978
No, that's not it.

928
00:59:14,448 --> 00:59:16,588
My father sent me a text.

929
00:59:19,388 --> 00:59:21,158
He said he has no intention
of coming back,

930
00:59:22,388 --> 00:59:24,088
and told us to stop looking for him.

931
00:59:27,458 --> 00:59:28,928
What do you think that means?

932
00:59:29,698 --> 00:59:31,568
My father and your mother...

933
00:59:32,838 --> 00:59:35,438
They're still together
and doing fine.

934
00:59:36,968 --> 00:59:38,238
I had no idea.

935
00:59:39,538 --> 00:59:42,348
And think about your father
and my mother.

936
00:59:42,978 --> 00:59:44,678
If they were to find out about this,

937
00:59:45,548 --> 00:59:47,648
the shock would be devastating,
don't you think?

938
00:59:54,618 --> 00:59:55,628
Seong Mi.

939
00:59:58,488 --> 01:00:00,498
What? Where did she go?

940
01:00:12,738 --> 01:00:13,738
Dae Han.

941
01:00:14,778 --> 01:00:18,808
I think it's for the best
if we break up.

942
01:00:19,648 --> 01:00:22,488
I'm so sorry.

943
01:00:33,928 --> 01:00:34,928
Honey.

944
01:00:36,168 --> 01:00:39,068
Hey, why are you out here?
Were you waiting for me?

945
01:00:40,938 --> 01:00:43,538
Your brother told me what happened.

946
01:00:43,868 --> 01:00:46,878
- That little punk!
- Honey, please.

947
01:00:49,848 --> 01:00:53,548
- Oh, Jeong Han. Seong Mi.
- Hey.

948
01:00:53,618 --> 01:00:55,648
You just had to go
and tell Seong Mi, didn't you?

949
01:00:56,188 --> 01:00:58,988
Honey, I'm the one who told him to.

950
01:00:59,258 --> 01:01:02,628
Hey!
Were you just being nice to her...

951
01:01:02,688 --> 01:01:04,928
- so she'd take your side?
- Jeong Han!

952
01:01:05,188 --> 01:01:07,028
Was it all just to get
their blessing to date Dong Suk?

953
01:01:07,098 --> 01:01:09,398
That's why you've been trying
to win Bucket over this whole time!

954
01:01:09,468 --> 01:01:11,528
Honey, please don't do this.

955
01:01:11,798 --> 01:01:14,098
Dae Han, are you going out?
Go on, hurry. Okay?

956
01:01:14,098 --> 01:01:16,108
Hey, take back what you just said.
Right now.

957
01:01:16,168 --> 01:01:18,838
Forget it.
You're breaking up with Dong Suk.

958
01:01:19,338 --> 01:01:21,938
I already told her to do the same.

959
01:01:22,678 --> 01:01:23,678
Honey.

960
01:01:23,978 --> 01:01:25,148
Hey, what did you just say?

961
01:01:26,078 --> 01:01:27,348
What did you just say?

962
01:01:27,648 --> 01:01:30,148
You met with Dong Suk?
Is that why she suddenly...

963
01:01:30,218 --> 01:01:32,758
- sent me that text to break up?
- Guys, please...

964
01:01:32,758 --> 01:01:37,128
She did? Well, I'm glad
at least one of you has some sense.

965
01:01:37,188 --> 01:01:38,688
- Hey!
- Unbelievable...

966
01:01:38,688 --> 01:01:41,628
Is Dae Han's girlfriend Dong Suk?

967
01:01:45,768 --> 01:01:46,768
Mom.

968
01:01:54,308 --> 01:01:55,308
Answer me.

969
01:01:55,948 --> 01:01:57,408
The person you're dating...

970
01:01:57,848 --> 01:01:59,778
Is it Dong Suk, Dr. Yang's sister?

971
01:02:13,058 --> 01:02:14,658
I'm sorry, honey.

972
01:02:16,068 --> 01:02:17,598
You must have been so shocked.

973
01:02:18,468 --> 01:02:19,468
No, it's okay.

974
01:02:20,198 --> 01:02:21,638
If anything, for telling me now...

975
01:02:22,308 --> 01:02:26,078
- I should be the one thanking you.
- No, thank you, honey.

976
01:02:27,438 --> 01:02:31,248
I'm so happy
that you trust me like this.

977
01:02:31,978 --> 01:02:33,248
I swear,

978
01:02:33,748 --> 01:02:36,318
I'll spend the rest of my life
making it up to you.

979
01:02:36,818 --> 01:02:38,318
You've been doing a great job
so far.

980
01:02:38,748 --> 01:02:39,818
I really...

981
01:02:40,658 --> 01:02:43,188
I was so worried
you were going to throw me out.

982
01:02:43,558 --> 01:02:45,228
Come on, of course not.

983
01:02:45,388 --> 01:02:48,258
What, did you think I was going to
ask for a divorce or something?

984
01:02:49,468 --> 01:02:50,468
Yes.

985
01:02:51,528 --> 01:02:53,038
So, really...
Just like this, can I still be...

986
01:02:54,038 --> 01:02:57,808
- Hyun Bin and Eun Bin's mother?
- Of course.

987
01:03:00,208 --> 01:03:01,408
Actually,

988
01:03:02,208 --> 01:03:05,208
I went to see a lawyer earlier.

989
01:03:05,748 --> 01:03:07,778
A lawyer? Why?

990
01:03:08,148 --> 01:03:13,018
To adopt Hyun Bin and Eun Bin,
we must contact their birth mother.

991
01:03:13,258 --> 01:03:15,118
Right.

992
01:03:15,888 --> 01:03:17,288
And rather than me
doing it directly,

993
01:03:17,558 --> 01:03:19,658
he said it would be better
to go through him.

994
01:03:20,028 --> 01:03:21,028
I see.

995
01:03:21,358 --> 01:03:24,398
So that's why you went
to see a lawyer.

996
01:03:25,398 --> 01:03:29,668
As I left, I saw a travel agency,
so I picked up a pamphlet.

997
01:03:29,868 --> 01:03:32,438
I want to go on a trip
with Eun Bin and Min Seo.

998
01:03:32,838 --> 01:03:34,838
That's a good idea.
Before Min Seo leaves,

999
01:03:35,178 --> 01:03:36,908
you all should definitely
go on a trip.

1000
01:03:37,778 --> 01:03:39,948
Do you want to come with us, too?

1001
01:03:40,348 --> 01:03:43,148
They have a starlight tour
in Gangneung.

1002
01:03:43,348 --> 01:03:45,118
I got the pamphlet. Hold on.

1003
01:03:45,548 --> 01:03:47,918
I know all about Gangneung.

1004
01:03:49,488 --> 01:03:51,388
- Hang on.
- What?

1005
01:03:54,258 --> 01:03:55,698
(Couples Tour)

1006
01:04:03,368 --> 01:04:05,238
Wow, this place looks great, too.

1007
01:04:05,808 --> 01:04:07,308
Where's the pamphlet?

1008
01:04:20,958 --> 01:04:23,128
Wow, this restaurant looks amazing.

1009
01:04:24,888 --> 01:04:26,898
Honey, what's wrong?

1010
01:04:30,568 --> 01:04:31,668
These...

1011
01:04:33,298 --> 01:04:35,338
- Oh, these...
- What is this?

1012
01:04:36,768 --> 01:04:38,568
What's this doing here?

1013
01:04:38,968 --> 01:04:39,978
You...

1014
01:04:41,808 --> 01:04:45,048
- You had me investigated?
- No, that's not it.

1015
01:04:46,848 --> 01:04:51,248
- So you knew everything all along.
- What? The thing is...

1016
01:04:52,488 --> 01:04:53,518
You...

1017
01:04:55,218 --> 01:04:56,658
You didn't trust me.

1018
01:04:57,958 --> 01:04:58,958
Even after all this time,

1019
01:05:00,828 --> 01:05:02,828
you still couldn't trust me.

1020
01:05:36,998 --> 01:05:39,598
(Recipe For Love)

1021
01:05:39,668 --> 01:05:42,838
I don't want to come
between you and your family.

1022
01:05:42,908 --> 01:05:46,638
If he's going to stay,
then I must be the one to leave.

1023
01:05:47,138 --> 01:05:49,548
- It's true. I hid it on purpose.
- Darn it!

1024
01:05:50,278 --> 01:05:51,748
Since I came into this house
with nothing,

1025
01:05:51,748 --> 01:05:53,848
- Oh, Mom!
- I'll leave with nothing, Father.

1026
01:05:53,918 --> 01:05:56,818
If this is really what you want,
I won't stand in your way.

1027
01:05:57,688 --> 01:06:00,188
From now on,
I'm just going to live for myself.

1028
01:06:00,458 --> 01:06:04,928
I, Gong Dae Han, love Yang Dong Suk.
Please allow us to be together.

1029
01:06:04,972 --> 01:06:06,572
Dramaday.me
